            "abstractNote": "This paper examines the taxonomy of the masked transarctic common shrew (Sorex cinereus) in the fauna of the USSR. Yudin reviews specimens from across Siberia, comparing their cranial and dental characters with North American populations. The study discusses geographic variation, diagnostic features, and the systematic position of Eurasian S. cinereus. The work clarifies the occurrence of this transarctic species in the USSR and provides a basis for subsequent faunal and biogeographic studies of Holarctic shrews.",
