                }
            ],
            "abstractNote": "From a detailed study of the skull of Nyetieejus emarginatus Dobson, currently known as Nyeticeius emarginatus (Dobson), it appears that it resembles the genus Seotomalles and differs from Nycticeius as regards the size and shape, presence of diastema between the upper canine and incisor, small size of the last upper molar, structure of the anterior edge of the orbit and lachrymal region and the presence of prominent sagittal and occipital crests. Further, it resembles the genus Scotomanes in external measurements. In spite of so much similarities, N. emarginatus differs from S. ornatus in its smaller forearm and tooth-rows and the absence of white spots on the body. It would appeal', therefore, that Nyetieejus emarginatus Dobson is best treated as a species under the genus Seotomanes as Scotomanes emarginatus (Dobson).",
